OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,FStroke victims are being "failed every
OL,7,Fday" because of gaps in rehabilitation
OL,8,Fcare caused by a shortage of staff,
OL,9,Fexperts have warned.
OL,11,FPatients' chances of recovery are
OL,12,F"limited" due to a lack of
OL,13,Fphysiotherapists and other support
OL,14,Fstaff, according to the Chartered
OL,15,FSociety of Physiotherapy (CSP) and the
OL,16,FAssociation of Chartered
OL,17,FPhysiotherapists in Neurology (ACPIN).
OL,26,@nD@ZOUoD@DO]tD@AOUtD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,FNational guidelines say people who
OL,7,Fhave had a stroke should receive
OL,8,Ftherapy-based rehabilitation for three
OL,9,Fhours a day, five days a week.
OL,11,FBut the CSP and the ACPIN said data
OL,12,Fsuggests that, on average, people
OL,13,Freceive rehab on only three to four
OL,14,Fdays a week in hospital and one to two
OL,15,Fdays once they leave hospital and are
OL,16,Fsupported at home.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,FA national survey of stroke
OL,7,Fphysiotherapists working in 159 NHS
OL,8,Fservices across the UK found workforce
OL,9,Fshortages across different aspects of
OL,10,Fstroke care.
OL,12,FThese included community stroke
OL,13,Fservices, acute stroke teams and
OL,14,Fcommunity rehabilitation support.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,FFindings from the 2025 Stroke
OL,7,FPhysiotherapy Workforce Survey suggest
OL,8,Fthere are 26% fewer physiotherapists
OL,9,Fthan national guidance recommends in
OL,10,Fcommunity stroke services, acute
OL,11,Fstroke teams are operating with 15%
OL,12,Ffewer physiotherapists than
OL,13,Frecommended, and community
OL,14,Frehabilitation support workers are 36%
OL,15,Fbelow guidance levels.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,FAsh James, director of practice and
OL,7,Fdevelopment at the CSP, said: "This
OL,8,Fdata shows that despite record numbers
OL,9,Fof registered physiotherapists, stroke
OL,10,Fservices in hospitals and the
OL,11,Fcommunity are unable to deliver the
OL,12,Fcare patients need because they are
OL,13,Fchronically understaffed.
OL,15,F"Something is going seriously wrong in
OL,16,Four health system if the NHS is
OL,17,Ffailing to turn workforce growth into
OL,18,Fthe posts required to meet even the
OL,19,Fminimum standards for stroke
OL,20,Frehabilitation.
OL,26,@oD@_OUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,F"It is deeply concerning that our
OL,7,Fmembers are going above and beyond to
OL,8,Fadvocate for their patients and secure
OL,9,Fthe staffing they need, only to have
OL,10,Ftheir concerns dismissed."
OL,12,FAdine Adonis, chairwoman of ACPIN,
OL,13,Fsaid: "More people are surviving
OL,14,Fstrokes in the UK than ever before,
OL,15,Fbut survival must be matched with the
OL,16,Fchance to recover well.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@ZO]uD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,F"These findings highlight a stark and
OL,7,Furgent gap in the number of
OL,8,Fphysiotherapists and support staff
OL,9,Favailable to provide the specialist
OL,10,Frehabilitation that stroke survivors
OL,11,Frely on. This is not good enough.
OL,13,F"It is failing people every day and
OL,14,Flimiting their potential for recovery.
OL,15,FWe need immediate action to ensure
OL,16,Fevery stroke survivor receives the
OL,17,Fphysiotherapy support they deserve."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUyD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,FDavid Stadelman, from Bournemouth,
OL,7,Fexperienced a life-threatening series
OL,8,Fof events including a stroke, heart
OL,9,Ffailure and major surgery, leaving him
OL,10,Funable to sit up, walk or carry out
OL,11,Fbasic daily tasks.
OL,13,FThe 73-year-old said: "I couldn't sit
OL,14,Fup in bed, brush my teeth or wash
OL,15,Fmyself. I was completely dependent on
OL,16,Fothers."
OL,18,FAfter four months in hospital, David
OL,19,Fwas discharged to a care home where he
OL,20,Fbegan four months of intensive
OL,21,Fphysiotherapy.
OL,26,@uD@WOUxD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,F"The physiotherapists were absolutely
OL,7,Fbrilliant. They worked with me four
OL,8,Ftimes a week and helped me relearn
OL,9,Feverything, from taking my first
OL,10,Fsteps, to walking up the stairs so I
OL,11,Fcould eventually go home," he said.
OL,13,F"They didn't just treat me, they gave
OL,14,Fme hope."
OL,16,FOnce home Mr Stadelman turned to a
OL,17,Flocal charity-run rehabilitation
OL,18,Fgroup, which he credits with helping
OL,19,Fhim regain independence.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@ZO]uD@AOUvD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,F"If I hadn't found that support, I
OL,7,Fdon't think I'd be doing half of what
OL,8,FI can now.
OL,10,F"I'm walking miles, I'm driving again,
OL,11,FI'm getting back to living my life.
OL,12,FBut that shouldn't depend on whether
OL,13,Fyou can find or afford something
OL,14,Foutside the NHS.
OL,16,F"It is very concerning to hear that
OL,17,Fstroke teams are not adequately
OL,18,Fstaffed to be able to support people
OL,19,Fin their recovery."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUxD@AOU{D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,FJuliet Bouverie, chief executive of
OL,7,Fthe Stroke Association, said: "Every
OL,8,Fday in the UK, around 240 people have
OL,9,Ftheir lives potentially destroyed by
OL,10,Fstroke.
OL,12,F"Stroke survivors are at risk of being
OL,13,Funable to see, speak, move or even
OL,14,Fswallow, which has a huge impact on
OL,15,Ftheir ability to enjoy a full and
OL,16,Findependent way of life.
OL,26,@oD@_OUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,F"We know that early and bespoke
OL,7,Frehabilitation, coupled with ongoing
OL,8,Fsupport, can vastly improve the
OL,9,Fphysical effects of stroke, and
OL,10,Ftherefore also support good emotional
OL,11,Fwellbeing.
OL,13,F"But there is no escaping the fact
OL,14,Fthat progress to improve the
OL,15,Favailability and intensity of
OL,16,Frehabilitation is far too slow.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775181806
OL,3,CStroke patients 'being failed every
OL,4,Cday' due to rehabilitation gaps
OL,6,F"Much greater investment in both
OL,7,Fpeople and processes to meet the
OL,8,Fnational guidelines of care are
OL,9,Fdesperately needed to ensure stroke
OL,10,Fsurvivors are supported both in
OL,11,Fhospital and the community for as long
OL,12,Fas they need it."
OL,14,FThe Department of Health and Social
OL,15,FCare has been approached for comment.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/13
